Les Dissonances appeared on the music scene in 2004 being, at the time, the only classical ensemble in which there was no conductor.
The conductor is the most important musician for musicians.
It is true, on the one hand, musicians need an education either to become soloists or to become performers in an orchestra – they are talking about instrumentalists, not composers.
They are trained as “specialized workers.”
They feel they need a leader.
On the other side of the stage, for the audience, all musical fetishization focuses on the conductor.
And so the business, the music industry, does its marketing.
We are no longer talking about music.
So if we look at this world, we have on the one hand skilled workers, which is stupid, and a public that can’t listen, but must watch, which is stupid,” Grimal said.
The violinist says that this change in the way he makes music came as a result of “musical disappointments” in his career as a soloist.
I was like a high-level athlete who had to do the same exercise around the world with different orchestras, to earn a lot of money and to bring money to the music industry.
Ten years ago, when I was about 30 years old, I found this very depressing, because I could no longer find human creativity and brotherhood in this system.
There is no point in continuing on this path.
