The rare disease a man suffers from
American Nick Hess was suspected by his family that he was an alcoholic, his wife even filming him when he was thirsty, could barely stand on his feet and his words were difficult to understand.
Although the 35-year-old said he did not drink alcohol, it was visible that he was drunk.
When she first accused me of being drunk without drinking, I thought she was crazy.
"But his friends and family thought, 'Maybe he drinks alone, he's a secret alcoholic,'" he told Mirror.
When he saw his wife’s footage with him, the man from Columbus, Ohio, simply didn’t recognize himself: “I was looking in my eyes and I wasn’t there.”
“It was terrible, I didn’t remember anything.”
In addition, his wife, who, despite doubting him for a while, eventually went with him to countless doctors, remembers that Nick’s breath also smelled like alcohol.
The moment that brought Nick the most to his mind was when, after a minor accident, when he was hit by another car, it was discovered that he had an alcoholemia three times the legal limits, although he had only drank one beer the night before.
After years and countless investigations, it was discovered that Nick suffered from an extremely rare disease, “Auto-brewery syndrome.”
Basically, the body causes all the carbohydrates consumed to ferment, turning into alcohol.
The one who suspected this could be Nick’s illness was his wife.
The disease has no cure yet, but since he quit carbohydrates, Nick has never had such episodes.
